stylometry: Optimization is finding the best fit decision. An example would be a company wanting to optimize their profit goal to best fit the company and their constraints within the company. The components of linear programming include - constraints; these are the factors that limit, and better help determine the final solver answer, changing cells - these are the factors that change according to the best fit solution - when solving you can enter in any set of numbers because solver will work on its own and change the figures that need to be in these cells ; nextly you have the goal which is usally something to do with profit - you highlight this cell gray and it is labeled  'Target Cell';
